sdp/prd-snapshot.md:81:| CCH-001 | Implement the Event dataclass with score-level, performance-level, reactive-delta, and provenance fields. | MUST | T1 | - `render/events.py` defines Event with event_id, phrase_id, section_id, voice_id, role, pitch, nominal_beat, nominal_dur_beats, harmonic_charge, melodic_charge, metric_weight, is_phrase_start/end, is_cadential, intent_tag, onset_sec, dur_sec, velocity, timing_deviation_ms, articulation, sensor_tempo_scale, sensor_amp_scale, sensor_brightness, rule_stack (list[str]), seed_path (tuple[int, ...])<br/>- score-level fields are immutable after render stage<br/>- dataclass is JSON-serializable and round-trips through OSC bundle encoding<br/>- unit tests verify field presence, immutability of score-level fields, and serialization round-trip |
sdp/prd-snapshot.md:85:| CCH-005 | Define Role enum (ostinato/melody/pad/perc/accent/silence) with grid_locked flag and role-filter policy used by all rules. | MUST | T1 | - Role enum exists with grid_locked boolean attribute (ostinato=True, perc=True, melody=False, pad=False, accent=False, silence=N/A)<br/>- every rule in the stack respects a shared `rule.applies_to(role)` filter so grid-locked voices skip R1–R8<br/>- tests verify grid-locked voices emerge from the render pass with timing_deviation_ms == 0 and no microtiming jitter |
sdp/prd-snapshot.md:91:| CCH-011 | Build the RenderPass framework: ordered rule stack with stable order, per-rule enable flags, per-rule quantity k, and role-filter gating. | MUST | T1 | - `render/pass_.py` defines RenderPass(rules, enabled_flags, quantities) with apply(score_tree, seeds) → PerformedPart<br/>- rule order is fixed and documented: R1→R2→R3→R4→R5→R6→R7→R8→R9→R10→R11→R12<br/>- per-rule k defaults to 1.0; authoring surface exposes overrides per-piece and per-intent-tag<br/>- tests verify stable order, k=0 equals rule-disabled, k=1 equals calibrated default |
sdp/prd-snapshot.md:92:| CCH-012 | Implement R1 Metric Accent: per-beat-position velocity multiplier applied only to non-grid-locked melodic/accent voices. | MUST | T1 | - `render/rules/metric_accent.py` applies 16-step 4/4 table [1.00, 0.82, 0.92, 0.80, 0.95, 0.80, 0.90, 0.78, 0.97, 0.80, 0.91, 0.78, 0.94, 0.80, 0.90, 0.78] with meter-aware extension to 3/4, 6/8, 5/4, 7/8<br/>- rule skips ostinato + perc by role filter<br/>- tests verify velocity distribution matches table on 4/4 melodic passage and is unchanged on ostinato |
sdp/prd-snapshot.md:95:| CCH-015 | Implement R4 Duration Contrast: exaggerate short-vs-long by log(dur_ratio_to_median), melodic roles only, capped at ±10%. | MUST | T1 | - `render/rules/duration_contrast.py` applies log-scaled multiplier within [0.90, 1.10] on melodic voices<br/>- ostinato / perc skipped<br/>- tests verify short notes shortened, long notes lengthened, and cap enforcement |
sdp/prd-snapshot.md:99:| CCH-019 | Implement R8 Microtiming Polish: per-note Gaussian jitter σ=3 ms on melodic, 1 ms on ostinato, 0 ms on grid-locked machine voices. | MUST | T1 | - `render/rules/microtiming.py` is the ONLY place white noise enters the pipeline<br/>- σ values below listener JND (10 ms) by design<br/>- grid-locked voices receive σ=0 and emerge with timing_deviation_ms==0<br/>- tests verify σ by role and zero-jitter on grid-locked |
sdp/prd-snapshot.md:100:| CCH-020 | Enforce role-filter gating across R1–R8 with a single shared contract; verify machine identity preservation end-to-end. | MUST | T1 | - all R1–R8 rules check `rule.applies_to(event.role)` before mutating the event<br/>- integration test: ostinato + melody passage renders with melody shaped and ostinato exactly quantized<br/>- gate test: passage where ostinato has non-zero timing_deviation_ms fails (indicates a rule leaked) |
sdp/prd-snapshot.md:101:| CCH-021 | Integrate partitura for phrase-feature extraction: harmonic_charge, melodic_charge, metric_weight, cadential detection, contour apex. | MUST | T1 | - `render/features.py` wraps partitura load_score + per-phrase feature computation<br/>- features annotated onto Events during score-tree → Event-list conversion<br/>- harmonic_charge uses tonal-pitch-space distance (Lerdahl) normalized 0..1<br/>- tests on known-score fixtures verify expected feature values |
sdp/prd-snapshot.md:115:| CCH-035 | Build anti-pattern tests: quantization ghosting, dynamic compression, motif ossification, random-as-expression (Ljung-Box), symmetric-arc uncanny, dead-silence failure. | MUST | T1 | - `render/antipatterns.py` implements each detector<br/>- quantization ghosting: velocity σ > 0 AND timing σ < 3 ms → fail<br/>- dynamic compression: velocity range < 20 → fail<br/>- motif ossification: GS > 0.95 across repeated sections → fail<br/>- random-as-expression: Ljung-Box fails to reject white noise on tempo or velocity series → fail<br/>- symmetric-arc uncanny: per-phrase worm convex-hull shape variance < 5% across phrases → fail<br/>- dead-silence failure: no rests ≥200 ms in a 2-minute melodic passage → fail<br/>- each detector has a positive fixture (should fail) and negative fixture (should pass) |
sdp/prd-snapshot.md:125:2. With R1–R8 enabled, single-voice melodic passages show structured velocity + timing deviations matching research pass bands (CCH-034).
sdp/prd-snapshot.md:126:3. Grid-locked voices (ostinato, perc) emerge from full-stack render with timing_deviation_ms == 0 — machine identity preserved.
sdp/prd-snapshot.md:128:5. Silence Budget (R10) enforces ≥100 ms silence at every phrase boundary on melodic voices in a 2-minute rendered fixture.
sdp/prd-snapshot.md:133:10. Metric battery + anti-pattern detectors integrated into CI; a deliberate regression (e.g., microtiming σ bumped to 50 ms, velocity range compressed to 5) fails the gate.
sdp/prd-snapshot.md:147:- **Senn et al. 2016 / Butterfield 2010** — groove microtiming within ±50 ms, mostly under 30 ms.
sdp/prd-snapshot.md:159:- **Forgetting machine identity.** If a rule leaks onto grid-locked voices, the render fails the role-filter gate.
sdp/prd-snapshot.md:163:- **Dead-silence failure.** A 2-minute melodic passage with no rests ≥200 ms fails — silence is a first-class voice.
